285 g Shaved Beef
2 unit(s) Sandwich Bun
113 g Mushrooms
56 g Onion, sliced
1 unit(s) Tomato
56 g Spring Mix
¾ cup Mozzarella Cheese, shredded
28 g Crispy Shallots
10 g Cream Sauce Spice Blend
2 unit(s) Beef Broth Concentrate
1 tbsp Balsamic Vinegar
0.13 tsp Sugar*
1 tbsp Oil*
0.13 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*
1 tbsp Butter*

Before starting, preheat the broiler to high. Wash and dry all produce.
Thinly slice mushrooms.
Cut tomato into 1/4-inch pieces.
To a large bowl, add half the vinegar, 1/8 tsp (1/4 tsp) sugar and 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil. Season with salt and pepper. Stir to combine. Place tomatoes and spring mix over top. Do not mix until step 4.
On an foil-lined baking sheet, arrange buns, cut-sides up. Sprinkle cheese over bottom buns.

Heat a large pot over high.
When the pot is hot, add 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) butter, mushrooms and onions. Season with salt and pepper. Cook for 3-4 min, stirring often, until tender.
Meanwhile, heat a large non-stick pan over high.
While the pan heats, line a plate with paper towels. Separate beef slices onto the prepared plate. Pat beef dry with paper towels, pressing to absorb as much moisture as possible.

Sprinkle Cream Sauce Spice Blend over mushrooms and onions. Stir to coat. Add broth concentrate and 1 cup ( 1 1/2 cups) water. Cook for 3-4 min, stirring occasionally, until sauce thickens slightly.
When the pan is hot, add 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil and beef. Cook for 1-2 min per side, stirring occasionally, until beef is golden and cooked through.** Remove from heat. Add remaining vinegar. Toss to coat.
Season with salt and pepper.

While beef cooks, toast buns in the top of the oven for 2-3 min, until cheese melts. (TIP: Keep an eye on buns, so they don't burn!)
Toss salad.
Top bottom buns with beef.
Using a slotted spoon, top beef with some of the mushrooms and onions. Sprinkle crispy shallots over top. Close with top buns.
Divide sandwiches, and salads between plates.
Serve remaining sauce alongside.